  "prompt": "What does worm meat taste like?",
  "response": "Worm meat is not commonly consumed in many parts of the world, so descriptions may vary based on limited experiences and cultural differences. Generally, people who have tasted worms tend to describe them as having an earthy or nutty flavor. The texture can be soft and slightly chewy, depending on the type of worm and how it is prepared. Some have compared worm meat to mushrooms or nuts because of its earthy taste. Ultimately, the flavor can vary depending on the worm's diet and preparation method.",
